Introduction

(Description of questions that are being investigated)

Research Questions

1)Which Level-1 services receive the most calls? 2)Which areas in Toronto most frequently require a call for services? 3)What are the average wait-times for calls for immediate-attention services (i.e.emergency services)?

Analysis

We are Connected Consulting Corp.and we are here to help FindHelp connect people and make sure all parties are having a successful and efficient experience. To begin with, we will seek and research thoroughly through the 211 Caller Data (2017-2019) to see variations between the different services being used as a Level-1 Category. Furthermore, we will measure and manipulate the average call-wait time for any call-centre services in Ontario and then study the original data provided by FindHelp to see if the emergency services and clients that have a severe situation are having their needs met in a timely manner.

Data

  1. To study the second outlook for this assessment, we have decided to look at the main 211 Caller data that will allow us to look at which communities required the most services and which communities need the most assistance. This will allow us to help those communities and improve their well being.

  2. To further study our third outlook on this assignment, we have chosen a secondary dataset found from the Ontario Data Catalogue. We found a dataset computed by ServiceOntario which puts together data based on calls handled and the average wait time per category of calls. ServiceOntario is one of the largest kiosk services funded and run by the government to serve the citizens of Ontario with their needs such as; Health card registration, Birth, marriage and death certificates, and Driver and vehicle licensing. We truly believe that the dataset from ServiceOntario is an essential source to the success of attempting to create calling services at FindHelp better or flow more efficiently.
